<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6387&amp;p=27818#p27818"><![CDATA[
Consideration Sure; however classic shell doesn't actually replace the windows shell <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> it just augments it. so having total control can be tricky at times. I dont actually know how difficult it would be, Im just stating that a solution is already available, in a piece of <strong>compatible</strong> freeware.. too much modification to the taskbar might break compatibility in unexpected ways.. Though Classic shell has been moving towards the taskbar in the last few updates (with a customizable skin and transparency), Those features were likely checked, and/or modified for compatibility with 7+<br /><br />Also my suggestion to start with taskscheduler probably wont work; however this should:<br /><br /><a href="http://answers.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/forum/windows_7-desktop/how-to-start-program-before-user-logon-windows-7/2bff97c4-c037-437c-9fa7-b143a3ae5189?auth=1" class="postlink">http://answers.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/forum/windows_7-desktop/how-to-start-program-before-user-logon-windows-7/2bff97c4-c037-437c-9fa7-b143a3ae5189?auth=1</a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=62">Jcee</a> — Tue Jul 26, 2016 12:49 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
