<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6387&amp;p=27813#p27813"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Windows 10 taskbar large icons]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6387&amp;p=27813#p27813"><![CDATA[
I searched the forum several times looking for anything about taskbar icons, but didn't see anything.<br /><br />I like Classic Shell and it's been a big blessing to me in both Win 8.1 and now 10.  However in Win 10, the taskbar icons are smaller than Win 8 and older.  I currently use a utility call &quot;7+ Taskbar Tweeker&quot; that has an option to &quot;use large taskbar icons in Win 10&quot;, and the utility runs at all times in the background in order to keep the taskbar icons at the requested size.<br /><br />StartIsBack++ has the same feature as 7+, and it runs better because somehow it does it a lower level, and when Windows starts, the taskbar icons are immediately the right size, whereas with the 7+ utility it can take a little bit for the adjustment to be made.<br /><br />In my opinion the taskbar is part of the &quot;shell&quot;, I request you to add this feature.<br /><br />Thanks.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=14331">Joorno</a> — Tue Jul 26, 2016 11:39 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
